for defense: 
in ubuntu run these commands
sudo apt install ufw
sudo ufw enable
sudo ufw allow ssh
sudo ufw allow from KALI_IP
sudo ufw status
sudo apt install wireshark
sudo wireshark


ufw: Calls the UFW command.
allow: Instructs UFW to allow the specified traffic.
ssh: The name of the service you want to allow (SSH, which typically operates on port 22). 
This ensures that SSH connections are permitted through the firewall, allowing you to remotely access your machine via SSHsudos
Use wireshark to trace and scan:
